<h2>
  Frequently Asked Questions
</h2>

<h3>
  How long is rental?
</h3>
<p>
<em>Two Weeks.</em> Just enough time to gather the friends for a couple of playthroughs and get to know the game beyond the first go.
</p>

<h3>
  But I am really enjoying the game and want to play more!
</h3>
<p>
  That's awesome. Let us know and we can extend the rental period if it is not on a waitlist for another customer.
</p>

<h3>
  Can I just keep the rental and pay you?
</h3>
<p>
  Most games do not have additional copies prepared for rental, so limitations apply.  But we may be able to accomate your request and charge a special used rate.  Contact us!
</p>

<h3>
  What happends if some pieces are missing or get lost?
</h3>
<p>
  It's okay, accidents happen.  Please leave a note on the feedback card, and we will do our best to fix it at no cost to you.
  But all games are checked-out with complete componets, so try your best to look around again.  We may have to charge a small fee if the gameplay is affected.
</p>

<h3>
  Can I vist the library and play there?
</h3>
<p>
  Not yet, but hopefully soon!  We just formed the library in fall 2021 and are working towards opening a store in Grand Rapids, Michigan.
</p>
